<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Remote" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Remote,</orth> 1) distant: <bibl n="shak. son 44.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 44, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pht 29" default="NO" valid="yes">Phoen. 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.31" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.148" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 5, 148</bibl>. With <emph>from</emph>: <cit><quote>from Athens is her house r. seven leagues,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 159</bibl></cit> (Ff <emph>removed</emph>). <cit><quote>r. from all the pleasures of the world,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.806" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 806</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) solitary, desert: <cit><quote>bear it to some r. and desert place,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.176" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 176</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>places r. enough are in Bohemia,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 3.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 31</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>